1. Install your liked OS. I prefer Debian Linux
2. In command lone use next command: python3 --version 
    if all correct then next step. Else install python3
3. Install git in your system. Also apt install git
4. Create folder workhistory. Also mkdir /home/user_name/workhistory
5. cd /home/user_name/workhistory
6. git clone https://github.com/saibogo/work_history.git
7. apt install pip
8. apt install python3-psycopg2
9. apt install python3-flask
10. apt install python3-requests
10. apt install python3-psutil
10. apt install python3-pandas
11. pip3 install fpdf
12. pip3 install aiogram==2.25.1 --break-system-packages 
13 create bot. get token and create file 'telegram_token.txt'
14 edit config.xml section path_to_telegram_token
15. apt install postgresql
16. su  (And insert your superuser password)
15. su - postgres
17. psql -Upostgres
18. =# CREATE USER saibogo WITH PASSWORD 'myPassword';
19. =# CREATE DATABASE workhistory;
20. =# GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE "workhistory" to saibogo;
21. =# \c workhistory
22. workhistory=# GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO "saibogo";
23. exit to normal terminal
    ALL owner in backup.db must be saibogo
24. psql  --username=saibogo --dbname=workhistory --host=localhost -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 --file=/path/to/file/postgress_backup.db
25. python3 /path/to/main.py --help
26. cd to static dir in your project
27. gzip -dr equips   This command unpack all details files
Well Done!
28. edit config.xml in your favorite editor (patches and ip)
29. python3 /path/to/main.py --help
30. python3 /path/to/main.py --allstart
31. in your browser go to to http://your_ip:5000
Well Done!

32. To add user in telegramm-bot add records in read_bot_access.py and write_bot_access.py
33. Server use HTTPS. Certificate and privateKey in folder wh_app/cert. Generated with using openssl

